64
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:18,520
First step is just to hover your drone.

65
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,340
You want to practice your throttle control.

66
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:25,920
Beginners tend to go up and down a lot, and this is, uh, it's really hard to land or bring your drone safely.

67
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,220
Take it out a little ways so I can actually hear myself talk.

68
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:32,600
So we're just going to practice staying at about the same height and hovering in the same spot.

69
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:39,680
And you notice I'm drifting to the right a little bit, so you're going to have to correct yourself by pushing a little bit to the left until we just stop and stay in the same position.

70
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,480
And I want to get a really nice constant hover.

71
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:48,340
You're going to have to adjust your throttle a bit up and down to try to keep your drone really, really, really still.

72
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:52,340
And with beginners, throttle control doesn't come naturally.

73
00:04:52,340 --> 00:04:58,200
They just want to put the stick at a certain spot, and they're going to end up going up, going down, and kind of bouncing back and forth and bunny hopping.

74
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:02,840
So throttle control is really important for FPV drones, so that's why we're learning it first.

75
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:15,200
So once you've learned how to hover really good, just using your throttle up and down and using your right pitch and roll stick to kind of stay in the same exact spot, the next step is going to be using our pitch and roll stick to move around.

76
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:21,600
Not using our yaw side to side, but we're going to be using our pitch and our roll sticks here.

77
00:05:21,740 --> 00:05:22,840
And we're going to have to use throttle.

78
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:27,660
We're going to have to use our throttle skills that we just learned to keep our drone in the air.

79
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:34,540
Because when you pitch to the side, your force is going to the side and not down directly, so you're going to have to use a little more throttle when you're going to the side.

80
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:48,160
Make sure you're in a big open field for that, and just kind of get the hang of flying forwards a bit, flying backwards, flying to the side, and keeping your drone not too high in the air and not crashing in the ground.

81
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:58,120
When you can pitch to the back, you can fly forwards, and you can fly side to side without losing too much altitude.

82
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:01,780
The next step we're going to do is incorporate our yaw.

83
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:04,580
So our yaw will actually spin it if I move it to the left here.

84
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:05,780
It'll spin our drone.

85
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:08,720
And we can use our yaw to make nice smooth turns.

86
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:20,020
So if I push my pitch stick forwards here and fly my drone forwards, I can now yaw to the side, and my drone will now be pointing in this new direction and flying in that new direction.

87
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:23,200
And that's how you do a turn with FPV in angle mode.

88
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,840
So with angle mode, you're going to want to bank a little as well.

89
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:33,340
So when we turn with our yaw, we're going to want to push our roll stick that way slightly as well.

90
00:06:33,340 --> 00:06:36,620
And this is just the same as your average motorcycle track.

91
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:44,880
If you do dirt biking or motorcycles, to get a really good turn without blowing out on the track, you need to bank into it a little bit.

92
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:47,340
So we're going to bank and yaw at the same time.

93
00:06:49,860 --> 00:06:52,060
In angle mode, though, you don't have to bank if you want.

94
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:54,920
You can just go straight forwards with your pitch stick and then yaw.

95
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:58,680
And your drone will turn around and start flying in the new direction.

96
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:03,760
So those are the three steps to learn how to fly your drone in angle mode.

97
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,080
You start off with the hover.

98
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:12,640
You get used to holding your drone at a good, nice altitude with your throttle and keeping it in that position with your pitch and your roll stick.

99
00:07:12,980 --> 00:07:21,120
Next step is learning how to actually move your drone around with your pitch and your roll stick while keeping it off the ground and keeping it from going too high in the air with your throttle.

100
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:25,680
And the third step is just adding that yaw in there that spins your drone from left and right.

101
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:28,960
So when you're going, you can actually turn and seeing where you're going.

102
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:37,220
And with that yaw step, it's important to add a little bit of banking in there so that you don't cut your turns too wide and your drone goes in hitting into the trees.

103
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:40,360
Because I'm going at this height and I just turn, I'll just go sideways into the tree here.

