00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:18,980
So I'm going to take my drone off and I'm going to bring it super high in the air and just show you how acro mode works really quick.

112
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:21,860
Now that we're really high in the air, I'm going to show you how this works.

113
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:28,440
Now, like I mentioned before, the stick position in acro mode correlates to how fast your drone is spinning, not an angle.

114
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:31,820
So if I move my stick all the way to the right, I'm just going to keep spinning.

115
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:37,880
And if I move my drone just a little bit to the right, I'm going to keep spinning at a slower speed.

116
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:42,720
And whenever I let go of my stick, my drone stops at whatever position I left it at.

117
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,360
I'll take it up high again and show you guys that.

118
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:53,860
So if I want to tilt my drone forwards, I need to push it forwards and then let go once I get to the certain angle that I want to be flying at forwards.

119
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:58,280
Then to go back to level, I need to pull backwards on my stick to get my drone back to level.

120
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:01,360
The cool thing about acro mode is you can do flips.

121
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:05,460
So I can just drop my throttle, spin it all the way around, and let go.

122
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:06,500
